HEADWORD: Nondecane
<hw>Non*dec"ane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nonus</ets> ninth + <ets>dec</ets>em ten.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A hydrocarbon of the paraffin series, a white waxy substance,
<chform>C19H40</chform>; -- so called from the number of carbon atoms in
the molecule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

